  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The USAID Ibyiringiro Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">People Living with HIV/AIDS (PLWHA)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of the Ibyiringiro project is to improve the quality of life for People Living with HIV &amp;amp; AIDS and vulnerable populations in 22 PEPFAR Districts by providing them with agricultural support.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall strategy of the Ibyiringiro project is the creation of a dynamic partnership among leading FDOs with broad based, community level HIV and AIDS activities and linkages to PEPFAR clinical partners and CHAMP. The proposed program is designed to provide assistance to community-based associations of PLWHA and their caregivers, which are currently recipients of food assistance, in order to build upon and enhance services available to association members and increase the number of PLWHA receiving more comprehensive palliative care and support at the community level.</narrative>
  </description>
